      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2002 BMW M3 (E46) represents a benchmark in mechanical preservation. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing, both verified for optimal operation. The high-revving 8,000 RPM redline is met with seamless power delivery through a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a Variable M Differential Lock. Crucially, the rear subframe has been inspected and remains in factory-perfect condition, free of stress fractures. The suspension geometry is crisp, retaining its original damping characteristics and bushing integrity. This is a collector-grade specimen with a pristine chassis and zero mechanical compromises.",
